	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-11-20T05:13:04">JPMorgan Smaller Companies Investment Trust plc is a United Kingdom-based investment trust company. The Company's objective is to achieve capital growth from the United Kingdom listed smaller companies by out-performance of the Company's benchmark index, The Financial Times Stock Exchange (FTSE) Small Cap Index (excluding investment trusts) and a rising share price over the longer term by taking carefully controlled risks. The Company's gearing policy is to operate within a range of -10% to +15% invested in normal markets. The Company does not invest more than 15% of its gross assets in other the United Kingdom listed investment companies, including investment trusts. The Company invests in a portfolio of investments in the United Kingdom and foreign smaller companies. It invests in various sectors, such as industrials, consumer services, technology, consumer goods, oil and gas, healthcare, financials and utilities. JPMorgan Funds Limited serves as the manager of the Company.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-10-16T10:48:19">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 31 July 2015, JPMorgan Smaller Cos Inv Trust PLC revenues increased 68% to L25.6M. Net income increased 79% to L23.3M. Revenues reflect Net Loss - Fin. Instruments Fair Value increase of 82% to L22M, Dividend Income increase of 14% to L3.5M, Property income distribution increase of 60% to L120K. Net income benefited from Other administrative expenses decrease of 21% to L77K (expense).</Text>
